President Joe Biden delivered a speech in Menlo, Iowa, discussing various topics including the recent mass shooting in New York City, the importance of biofuels, efforts to lower costs for American families, and investments in infrastructure. He highlighted the role of biofuels in supporting farmers, creating jobs, reducing reliance on foreign oil, and promoting a sustainable energy future. He also announced plans to issue an emergency waiver to allow the sale of E15 gasoline that uses more ethanol across the United States. Additionally, President Biden emphasized the need to address food prices, invest in clean water systems, improve access to high-speed internet, and repair bridges. He expressed optimism about the future of America and encouraged individuals to keep the faith and spread it to others.